Why Mayo Clinic 
Join the authority in medicine and partner with the nation's best hospital (U.S. News & World Report 2020-2021), ranked #1 in more specialties than any other care provider. At Mayo Clinic, we believe there is a better path to healing that humanizes the practice of health care and inspires hope in the people who need it most. You will be part of an amazing diverse team committed to solving the most serious and complex medical challenges - one patient at a time.
 Mayo Clinic offers a variety of employee benefits. For additional information please visit Mayo Clinic Benefits . Eligibility may vary. 
Position description 
The department of Radiology at Mayo Clinic Florida is seeking a fellowship-trained academic neuroradiologist to join a team of 12 CAQ certified neuroradiology consultants. This is a full-time position for an academically ambitious candidate with strong diagnostic skills in all facets of neurological imaging including MR, CT, and US. Additional experience with advanced applications of MR, ultra-high field MR (7T), quantitative image processing and informatics is preferred. The Neuroradiology Division closely supports colleagues in Neurology, Neurosurgery, ENT and Orthopedic surgery. Multidisciplinary conferences, education and research programs in Neurosurgery, Epilepsy, Head/Neck and Spine are an integral part of the neuroradiology service. The candidate will be expected to perform routine image-guided procedures and actively participate in education and research. 
Mayo Clinic Florida is one of the nation's best hospital (U.S. News & World Report 2017-2018), ranked #1 in more specialties than any other health system. The radiology department is home to cutting edge diagnostic and research infrastructure including a clinical 7T MR, cyclotron, and artificial intelligence lab. Practicing at Mayo Clinic provides a rewarding career that supports and promotes excellence in patient-centered care, translational research, and mentorship for young faculty. You can thrive in an environment that promotes innovation by providing a wealth of resources- including an integrated EMR, international patient referral and collaboration with top clinical and radiology specialists. The neuroradiology division publishes over 40 peer-reviewed research papers every year. 
License or certification 
Radiology board-certification and neuroradiology CAQ eligibility are required. 
